858 auto throwScope = DECLARE_THROW_SCOPE(vm);

864 EnsureStillAliveScope argument0 = callFrame->uncheckedArgument(0);

866 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(throwScope, encodedJSValue());
867 EnsureStillAliveScope argument1 = callFrame->uncheckedArgument(1);
868 auto script = convert<IDLDOMString>(*lexicalGlobalObject, argument1.value());
869 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(throwScope, encodedJSValue());
870 RELEASE_AND_RETURN(throwScope, JSValue::encode(toJS<IDLUndefined>(*lexicalGlobalObject, throwScope, [&]() -> decltype(auto) { return impl.setStandardFontFamily(WTFMove(family), WTFMove(script)); })));
871}

1462JSC::IsoSubspace* JSInternalSettings::subspaceForImpl(JSC::VM& vm)
1463{
1464 auto& clientData = *static_cast<JSVMClientData*>(vm.clientData);
1465 auto& spaces = clientData.subspaces();
1466 if (auto* space = spaces.m_subspaceForInternalSettings.get())
1467 return space;
1468 static_assert(std::is_base_of_v<JSC::JSDestructibleObject, JSInternalSettings> || !JSInternalSettings::needsDestruction);
1469 if constexpr (std::is_base_of_v<JSC::JSDestructibleObject, JSInternalSettings>)
1470 spaces.m_subspaceForInternalSettings = makeUnique<IsoSubspace> ISO_SUBSPACE_INIT(vm.heap, vm.destructibleObjectHeapCellType.get(), JSInternalSettings);
1471 else
1472 spaces.m_subspaceForInternalSettings = makeUnique<IsoSubspace> ISO_SUBSPACE_INIT(vm.heap, vm.cellHeapCellType.get(), JSInternalSettings);
1473 auto* space = spaces.m_subspaceForInternalSettings.get();
1474IGNORE_WARNINGS_BEGIN("unreachable-code")
1475IGNORE_WARNINGS_BEGIN("tautological-compare")
1476 void (*myVisitOutputConstraint)(JSC::JSCell*, JSC::SlotVisitor&) = JSInternalSettings::visitOutputConstraints;
1477 void (*jsCellVisitOutputConstraint)(JSC::JSCell*, JSC::SlotVisitor&) = JSC::JSCell::visitOutputConstraints;
1478 if (myVisitOutputConstraint != jsCellVisitOutputConstraint)
1479 clientData.outputConstraintSpaces().append(space);
1480IGNORE_WARNINGS_END
1481IGNORE_WARNINGS_END
1482 return space;
1483}

1485void JSInternalSettings::analyzeHeap(JSCell* cell, HeapAnalyzer& analyzer)
1486{
1487 auto* thisObject = jsCast<JSInternalSettings*>(cell);
1488 analyzer.setWrappedObjectForCell(cell, &thisObject->wrapped());
1489 if (thisObject->scriptExecutionContext())
1490 analyzer.setLabelForCell(cell, "url " + thisObject->scriptExecutionContext()->url().string());
1491 Base::analyzeHeap(cell, analyzer);
1492}

1503JSC::JSValue toJSNewlyCreated(JSC::JSGlobalObject*, JSDOMGlobalObject* globalObject, Ref<InternalSettings>&& impl)
1504{
1505
1506#if ENABLE(BINDING_INTEGRITY)
1507 const void* actualVTablePointer = getVTablePointer(impl.ptr());
1508#if PLATFORM(WIN)
1509 void* expectedVTablePointer = __identifier("??_7InternalSettings@WebCore@@6B@");
1510#else
1511 void* expectedVTablePointer = &_ZTVN7WebCore16InternalSettingsE[2];
1512#endif
1513
1514 // If this fails InternalSettings does not have a vtable, so you need to add the
1515 // ImplementationLacksVTable attribute to the interface definition
1516 static_assert(std::is_polymorphic<InternalSettings>::value, "InternalSettings is not polymorphic");
1517
1518 // If you hit this assertion you either have a use after free bug, or
1519 // InternalSettings has subclasses. If InternalSettings has subclasses that get passed
1520 // to toJS() we currently require InternalSettings you to opt out of binding hardening
1521 // by adding the SkipVTableValidation attribute to the interface IDL definition
1522 RELEASE_ASSERT(actualVTablePointer == expectedVTablePointer);
1523#endif
1524 return createWrapper<InternalSettings>(globalObject, WTFMove(impl));
1525}
